# 11. Why this is a direct demonstration rather than a new theory

This document does not introduce new operator meanings. It applies the existing parser to selected folios. The same values are used across PROCESS, SPECIAL/ASTRO, ASTRO, and BALNEO contexts.

The evidential force is combinatorial. The model must be correct not only in isolated sign meanings, but also in sign order, positional behavior, key-page regime, visual correspondence, and semantic coherence across running text. A free-association model would have to explain why the same inventory repeatedly produces coherent readings across different key-page types and visual regimes.

---

# 12. Provisional conclusion

This side paper is not a new parser. It demonstrates how the established parser is used for translation.

The selected demonstrations should therefore balance explanation and application: one key page to show the internal reading aid, and several ordinary or recipe-like pages to show that the parser works as a direct reading system. A normal herbal folio, a balneo folio, a pharma/vessel folio, and a final compressed star/text folio together provide a stronger demonstration than key pages alone.

The strongest conservative conclusion is that the manuscript contains both internal reading aids and applied recipe/procedure pages. The key pages show how an initiated reader should apply the grammar. The ordinary pages show the grammar in use. The final text-heavy pages may represent the most compressed form of the notation: minimal visual support, maximum structural encoding.

The demonstration therefore supports the central claim of the main paper: Voynichese is complete at the structural-functional level, while remaining incomplete or refinable at the historical-lexical level.
